<_X_chapter sid="NEH 12">
<verse sid="NEH 12:1"/>(2Esdras 22.1) And these are the priests and the Leuites who went up with Zorobabel son of Salathiel and Iesous: Saraia, Iermia, Esdra;<verse eid="NEH 12:1"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:2"/>Amaria, Malouch;<verse eid="NEH 12:2"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:3"/>Sechenia.<verse eid="NEH 12:3"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="NEH 12:4"/>&amp;#x2013;<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:4</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="NEH 12:4"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="NEH 12:5"/><char style="no">&amp;#x2013;</char><note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:5</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="NEH 12:5"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="NEH 12:6"/>&amp;#x2013;<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:6</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="NEH 12:6"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:7"/>These were the rulers of the priests and their brothers in the days of Iesous.<verse eid="NEH 12:7"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:8"/>And the Leuites: Iesou, Banoui, Kadmiel, Sarabia, Iodae, Maththania. He was over<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:8</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'in charge of'</char></note> the hands, and their brothers were in the daily divisions.<verse eid="NEH 12:8"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="NEH 12:9"/><char style="no">&amp;#x2013;</char><note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:9</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="NEH 12:9"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:10"/>And Iesous begat Ioakim, and Ioakim begat Eliasib, and Eliasib, Iodae;<verse eid="NEH 12:10"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:11"/>and Iodae begat Ionathan and Ionathan begat Iadou.<verse eid="NEH 12:11"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:12"/>And in the days of Ioakim, his brothers, the priests and chiefs of paternal families were: for Saraia, Amaria; for Iermia, Hanania;<verse eid="NEH 12:12"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:13"/>for Esdra, Mesoulam; for Amaria, Ioanan;<verse eid="NEH 12:13"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:14"/>for Amalouch, Ionathan; for Sechenia, Ioseph;<verse eid="NEH 12:14"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:15"/>for Harem, Hannas; for Marioth, Helkai;<verse eid="NEH 12:15"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:16"/>for Addai, Zacharias; for Ganathoth, Mesoulam;<verse eid="NEH 12:16"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:17"/>for Abia, Zechri; for Beniamin, in the times of Peleti;<verse eid="NEH 12:17"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:18"/>for Balga, Samoue; for Semeias, Ionathan;<verse eid="NEH 12:18"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:19"/>for Iarim, Maththania; for Idia, Ozi;<verse eid="NEH 12:19"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:20"/>for Salai, Kallai; for Amek, Abed;<verse eid="NEH 12:20"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:21"/>for Helkia, Hasabias; for Iedeiou, Nathanael.<verse eid="NEH 12:21"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:22"/>The Leuites, in the days of Eliasib, Ioada and Ioa and Ioanan and Idoua, were recorded as the chiefs of paternal families and priests in the reign of Darius the Persian:<verse eid="NEH 12:22"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:23"/>sons of Leui were chiefs of paternal families, having been recorded in the book of the words of the days, even until the days of Ionan son of Elisoue.<verse eid="NEH 12:23"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:24"/>And the rulers of the Leuites, Hasabia and Sarabia and Iesou and sons of Kadmiel, and their brothers were over against them, to sing hymns and to praise, by the commandment of Dauid the man of God, class with class;<verse eid="NEH 12:24"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:25"/>when I gathered the gatekeepers<verse eid="NEH 12:25"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:26"/>in the days of Ioakim son of Iesous son of Iosedek and in the days of Neemias. And Esdras was the priest and the scribe.<verse eid="NEH 12:26"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:27"/>And at the rededications of the wall of Ierousalem they sought the Leuites in their places, to bring them to Ierousalem, to celebrate the rededications and the merriment with thodatha<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:27</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'thanksgivings'</char></note> and with odes, while playing the cymbal and harps and cinyras<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:27</char><char closed="false" style="ft">= Hebrew 'kinnor' = 'lyre'</char></note>.<verse eid="NEH 12:27"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:28"/>And the sons of the singers and some from the region that circles around Ierousalem and some from villages<verse eid="NEH 12:28"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:29"/>and some from the fields gathered, because the singers in Ierousalem built the villages for themselves.<verse eid="NEH 12:29"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:30"/>And the priests and the Leuites were purified, and they purified the people, the gatekeepers and the wall.<verse eid="NEH 12:30"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:31"/>And they brought the rulers of Iouda up onto the wall and appointed two great ones<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:31</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'companies'; Greek = masc.</char></note> concerning praise and went through to the right on the wall of dung;<verse eid="NEH 12:31"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:32"/>and after them went Hosaia and half the rulers of Iouda<verse eid="NEH 12:32"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:33"/>and Azarias, Esdra and Mesoulam;<verse eid="NEH 12:33"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:34"/>Iouda and Beniamin and Samaias and Ieremia<verse eid="NEH 12:34"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:35"/>and some of the sons of priests with trumpets: Zacharias son of Ionathan-- being a son of Samaia-- being a son of Maththania-- being a son of Michaia-- being a son of Zakchour-- being a son of Asaph;<verse eid="NEH 12:35"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:36"/>and his brothers were Samaia and Oziel, Gelolia, Maaia, Nathanael and Ioudas, Hanani, so that they might sing with the songs of Dauid the man of God, and Esdras the scribe was in front of them<verse eid="NEH 12:36"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:37"/>at the gate of Ain, opposite them, and they went up to the stairs of the city of Dauid, in the ascent of the wall above the house of Dauid and as far as the gate of water in the east.<verse eid="NEH 12:37"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:38"/>And concerning praise, the second one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:38</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'company'; Greek = fem</char></note> meeting them went out, and I followed it, and half of the people were on the wall above the tower of the Thennorim even as far as the broad wall<verse eid="NEH 12:38"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:39"/>and above the gate of Ephraim and to the Eisiana gate and to the fish gate and at the tower of Hanameel and from the tower of Mea, even as far as the sheep gate, and they stood in the gate of the guard.<verse eid="NEH 12:39"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:40"/>And the two<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:40</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'companies'; Greek = fem</char></note> of praise stood in the house of God, and I and half of the generals with me<verse eid="NEH 12:40"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:41"/>and the priests Eliakim, Maasias, Beniamin, Michaias, Elionai, Zacharias, Hananias<verse eid="NEH 12:41"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:42"/>and Semeias and Eleazar and Ozias and Ioanna and Melchias and Ailam and Ezour and the singers were heard and reviewed.<verse eid="NEH 12:42"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:43"/>And they offered great sacrifices on that day and rejoiced, because God made them rejoice greatly, and their wives and their children rejoiced, and the joy in Ierousalem was heard from far away.<verse eid="NEH 12:43"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:44"/>And on that day they appointed men over the treasure chambers for stores, for the first fruits and for the tithes and for the things collected in them for the rulers of the cities, portions for the priests and for the Leuites, because there was joy in Iouda both over the priests and over the Leuites that stood<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">12:44</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'were appointed'</char></note>.<verse eid="NEH 12:44"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:45"/>And they guarded the guard stations of the house of their God and the guard stations for purification and the singers and the gatekeepers, according to the commandments of Dauid and his son Salomon.<verse eid="NEH 12:45"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:46"/>Because in the days of Dauid, Asaph from the beginning was the first of those that sing both hymn and praise to God;<verse eid="NEH 12:46"/>

<verse sid="NEH 12:47"/>and in the days of Zorobabel all Israel was giving portions for the singers and the gatekeepers, the rule of a day for its day, and were sanctifying for the Leuites, and the Leuites were sanctifying for sons of Aaron.<verse eid="NEH 12:47"/>
</_X_chapter>




